Cherkasy Oblast

Sofiyivka Park

One of the most beautiful parks in Ukraine.The park accounts for over 2000 types of trees, bushes and flowers, both local and exotic, which harmonically co-exist with beautiful pounds, lakes, waterfalls and rocks.

Geolocation

Buky Canyon

It is approximately 5 km (3.1 mi) long, 20 m (66 ft) deep.it attracts many tourists. Someone comes to admire the rocky shores buky canyon, and other picnics on numerous meadows on both sides of the river

Geolocation

Maksym Zaliznyak oak tree

Being over 1,100 year old, it is one of the oldest and biggest trees in Ukraine and Europe. It is named after Maksym Zalizniak, a leader of the Koliivshchyna rebellion of haidamaks in 1768. Its trunk is 9 meters (in circumference); its height is about 30 metres (98 ft).

Chernihiv Oblast

Blue Lakes

The Blue Lakes are the result of industrial activity of a person. Over time, the industrial process was stopped because the workers reached the artesian layer. As a result, all the careers of the neighborhood were filled with water from the bowels of the earth, which has unique healing properties.

Geolocation

Palace of Hetman Kyrylo Rozumovskyi

Kyrylo Rozumovsky was Hetman of Ukraine from 17501764. During his hetmanship the city of Baturyn became the hetman's capital. Now it is a museum of the National Historical and Cultural Reserve Hetman's Capital.

Geolocation

Baturyn Fortress Citadel

The Citadel of the Baturyn Fortress is one of the most important historical values of the city of Baturyn, which was the capital of Ukrainian hetmans in the 17th-18th centuries.

Chernivtsi Oblast

Yuriy Fedkovych Chernivtsi National University

University was founded in 1875.The architectural ensemble of the main campus of the university, the Residence of Bukovinian and Dalmatian Metropolitans, is included on the list of UNESCO World Heritage Sites.

Geolocation

Cut Stones

Protyati Kameni (literally: Cut Stones) is a group of picturesque rocks in Pokutsko-Bukovina Carpathians. The geological monument of nature.

Geolocation

The Shurdyn pass

The Shurdyn pass is one of the highest car passes in Ukraine, the height of which is 1173 m. It passes through the Rakov mountain range between the settlements of Selyatyn and Berehomet. Here are harsh high mountains with steep cliffs.

Crimea

Vorontsov Palace

The Vorontsov Palace is one of the oldest and largest palaces in Crimea, and is one of the most popular tourist attractions on Crimea's southern coast.

Geolocation

Ai-Petri Mountain

Ai-Petri is a peak in the Crimean Mountains.It is one of the windiest places in Crimea.In order to see these fantastic panoramas, numerous travelers climb the Ai-Petri all year round.

Geolocation

Swallow's Nest

Palace was built between 1911 and 1912, on top of the 40-metre-high Aurora Zliff. The Swallow's Nest is one of the most popular visitor attractions in Crimea, having become the symbol of Crimea's southern coastline.

Geolocation

Dnipropetrovsk Oblast

Petrykivka painting

Petrykivka painting is a traditional Ukrainian decorative painting style, originating from the village of Petrykivka in Dnipropetrovsk oblast of Ukraine.The earliest known examples of this style date from the 18th century, but it continues to thrive and develop as a modern art form.

Geolocation

Tarom quarry

Tarom quarry is prohibited for swimming. Previously, granite was mined here, but later this business was abandoned, and the quarry was filled with water. What is its depth - no one can say for sure, they say that it is about 10 meters.

Geolocation

Dnipro embankment

The Dnipro embankment is one of the longest in Europe. Its total length is about 32 km.

Geolocation

Donetsk Oblast

Stone graves

Monumental rock middle of the steppe. Unique granites have no analogues in the world on the chemical composition and physical structure.

Geolocation

Sviatohirsk Lavra

The Holy Assumption Sviatohirsk Lavra (also known as The Holy Mountains Lavra, Sviatohirsk Cave Monastery), an important spiritual center of eastern Ukraine was first mentioned in written sources in 1526.

Geolocation

Soledar Salt Mine

Soledar Salt Mine is a complex of man-made mines of Artyomsalt company. The system of galleries at a depth of about 300 m (985 ft) is a result of more than 100 years of underground works. Extends to 200 km (124 miles).

Ivano-Frankivsk Oblast

The Rocks of Dovbush

The Rocks of Dovbush is a group of natural and man-made structures carved out of rock at around 980 m.The name of the formations comes from a leader of the opryshky movement, Oleksa Dovbush.

Geolocation

Bukovel

Bukovel is known as one of the most famous and ultramodern ski resort in Ukraine. This recreational haven owes its enormous popularity among both Ukrainian and foreign lovers of outdoor activities to its climate, endless comforts, and plenty of well-equipped skiing trails.

Geolocation

Maniava waterfall

Waterfall is one of the highest waterfalls in the Ukrainian Carpathians and is located in the Gorgany mountain ridge in Ukraine.Its height is nearly 20 metres.

Kharkiv Oblast

Cretaceous mountains

It is represented by a long ridge of chalk hills, similar to miniature chalk mountains stretching for several tens of kilometers along the Oskil river.

Geolocation

Oleksiivska fortress

Oleksiivska fortress is one of the fortification structures of the Ukrainian defense line, that was built in the XVIII century for protection against enemy attacks. Earthwork is well preserved and give a complete picture of the shape and size of such fortresses.

Geolocation

Sharivka palace

"Sharivka" is the most gourgeous palace complex in the eastern Ukraine, a real miracle of a gardening and park art.

Kherson Oblast

Lake Lemuria

Small lake in the western part of Syvash Bay. Lemuria lake has pink water due to the action of an algae which produces large amounts of beta-carotene. Lake Lemuria is a healing resort of international importance.

Geolocation

Askania-Nova

Ukrainian nature reserve consists of a zoological park, a botanical (dendrological) garden, and an open territory of virgin steppes.

Geolocation

Oleshky Sands

Oleshky Sands, is the largest expanse of sand in Ukraine and the second-largest in Europe. The 161 square-kilometer expanse of semi-arid desert.Dunes rise up to 5 meters above the surrounding sand and punctuate the landscape.

Khmelnytskyi Oblast

Podilski Tovtry National Nature Park

The park's area covers 2,613.16 km2.There are 1,700 different types of flora, 60 of which are included in the Red Book of Ukraine. Also, there are 217 different types of fauna, 29 of which are included in the Red Book of Ukraine as well.

Geolocation

Kamianets-Podilskyi Castle

Historical accounts date Kamianets-Podilskyi Castle to the early 14th century, although recent archaeological evidence has proved human existence in the area back to the 12th or 13th century. Initially built to protect the bridge connecting the city with the mainland.

Geolocation

Atlantyda Cave

Atlantyda is a karst cave in Ukraine, most famous for its unusual geology, rare formations, and pristine condition.The cave is 2525 m long and 18 m deep, with 4440 m area.

Kyiv Oblast

Trypillia culture

Near Trypillia an archaeologist Vikentiy Khvoyka discovered an extensive Neolithic site of the Cucuteni-Trypillian culture.The name Trypillia means 'three fields' in the Slavic languages.

Geolocation

Arsenalna metro station

The station was opened along with the first stage and is currently the deepest station in the world at 105.5 metres. This fact caused by landscape characteristic.

Geolocation

The Kyiv Sea

The Kyiv Reservoir (locally the Kyiv Sea) is a large water reservoir located on the Dnieper River in Ukraine. Named after the city of Kyiv, which lies to the south, it covers an area of 922 square kilometres within the Kyiv Oblast.

Kirovohrad Oblast

Coal mine Morozov

Abandoned opencast brown coal mine Morozovskiy is the enterprise is under liquidation, coal mining is not carried out for 5 years, despite the fact that the brown coal reserves are sufficient for at least another 20 years of active mining.

Geolocation

Strategic missile forces museum

Military museum was built around the remains of a former underground Unified Command Post (UCP) for RT-23/SS-24 Molodets ICBM rockets.In 1994 Ukraine agreed to destroy the weapons, and to join the Treaty on the Non-Proliferation of Nuclear Weapons (NPT).

Geolocation

Tract "Cascades"

Unique landscape shapes was formed due to the main tectonic structure of Ukraine called Ukrainian crystalline shield. It stretches for a thousand kilometers, and has unusual natural attractions.

Lviv Oblast

The Fortress of Tustan

Tustan was a Medieval cliff-side fortress-city and customs site of the 9th16th centuries, an Old Rus cliff-side defensive complex.Tustan was a defence and administrative center as well as a customs site on the important salt route leading from Drohobych through Transcarpathia to Western Europe.
